# =============================================================================
# kapa.env — OPTIONAL and NOT needed for standard operation.
# (English twin of kapa.env.example.)
# =============================================================================
# The configuration model is deliberately simple:
#   * all non-secret settings              -> config/kapa.ini
#   * passwords/keys                       -> separate .pass files (path in the INI)
#   * business data (roles/teams/mail rules) -> admin UI
#
# The shipped systemd unit does NOT read this file anymore (no
# EnvironmentFile) – it only calls `--config /etc/kapa/kapa.ini --serve`.
#
# This template is only relevant if you prefer to set passwords via
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES instead of .pass files (e.g. when starting by hand or
# in a container). Precedence: parameter > .pass file > env. Export the
# variable before the script starts:
#
#   ARIA_PASSWORD=...           # instead of password-file in the INI
#   AD_BIND_PASSWORD=...        # instead of ad-bind-password-file
#   SMTP_PASSWORD=...           # instead of smtp-password-file
#   BACKUP_PASSWORD=...         # instead of backup-password-file
#
# Recommendation: with systemd, use the .pass files (root:kapa, 0640) – then
# this file is not needed at all.
# =============================================================================
